The paper deals with vision-based autonomous driving and proposes a method for integrating gaze information into a deep driving network. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of a simulator, which suggests that it may also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The paper also involves the use of deep neural networks, which suggests that it may belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the benefits of gaze information for human learners, which suggests that it may also belong to the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
